[b]Gary Lineker introduces highlights and reaction to the day's seven Premier League matches. Sunderland welcome Manchester United to the Stadium of Light looking to improve on a record that has seen the Black Cats win only two of their last 26 games against the Red Devils in all competitions. Early season strugglers Chelsea meet Newcastle at Stamford Bridge. The two sides played out an entertaining 2-2 at St. James' Park earlier in the season with the visitors scoring twice in the last 11 minutes to rescue a point. The day's other matches see Bournemouth play Stoke, Crystal Palace entertain Watford, Everton face West Brom, West Ham travel to Norwich and Swansea meet Southampton. [/b]
